  "description": "The dish uses South Indian evening-tiffin logic: quick-cooking grains, legumes, and aromatic tempering for depth without richness. Samai Vegetable Uttappam brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Heat a tawa on medium heat and grease lightly.",
    "Pour a ladle of batter into a thick round, scatter the vegetables over the top, and press gently.",
    "Cook 3 minutes on medium-low heat until the bottom turns golden and the top starts to set.",
    "Flip and cook 1 minute on low heat, then serve with tomato chutney."
